<bibRefCitation id="EF859AC183777E08A178FBD1B4D6691C" author="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q." box="[559,747,1096,1122]" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref8869" refString="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q. (1998) On the genus Megalotomus Fieber from China (Heteroptera: Alydidae). Entomologische Berichten, Amsterdam, 58 (3), 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1998">Liu &amp; Liu, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Among these, seven species occur in the Palaearctic Region, with only 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB383777E08A25FFBF4B45369F9" authority="(Say, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[264,622,1132,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinquespinosus">
<emphasis id="B9603B2283777E08A25FFBF4B7D569F8" box="[264,488,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="212">M. quinquespinosus</emphasis>
(Say, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
recorded from the Nearctic Region. A new combination transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB383777E08A3C0FB09B6DE69D4" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[151,227,1168,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Alydus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9603B2283777E08A3C0FB09B6DE69D4" box="[151,227,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="212">Alydus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB383777E08A250FB09B7A269D4" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Fieber" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[263,415,1168,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9603B2283777E08A250FB09B7A269D4" box="[263,415,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="212">Megalotomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a new junior synonym are proposed below.
